def pickle_img():
    import pickle
#     folder_benign_train = 'data/train/benign'
#     folder_malignant_train ='data/train/malignant'
    
#     folder_basal_train ='data/train/basal cell carcinoma'
#     folder_benign_test = 'data/test/benign'
    
#     folder_malignant_test = 'data/test/malignant'
#     folder_basal_test ='data/test/basal cell carcinoma'
    folder_actinic_train = 'data/224x224/train/actinic keratosis'
    folder_melanoma_train ='data/224x224/train/melanoma'
    folder_basal_train ='data/224x224/train/basal cell carcinoma'
    folder_nevus_train = 'data/224x224/train/nevus'
    folder_pigmented_train ='data/224x224/train/pigmented benign keratosis'
    folder_seborrheic_train ='data/224x224/train/seborrheic keratosis'
    folder_squamous_train ='data/224x224/train/squamous cell carcinoma'
    folder_vascular_train ='data/224x224/train/vascular lesion'

    
    folder_actinic_test = 'data/224x224/test/actinic keratosis'
    folder_melanoma_test = 'data/224x224/test/melanoma'
    folder_basal_test ='data/224x224/test/basal cell carcinoma'
    folder_nevus_train = 'data/224x224/train/nevus'
    folder_pigmented_train ='data/224x224/train/pigmented benign keratosis'
    folder_seborrheic_train ='data/224x224/train/seborrheic keratosis'
    folder_squamous_train ='data/224x224/train/squamous cell carcinoma'
    folder_vascular_train ='data/224x224/train/vascular lesion'


    read = lambda imname: np.asarray(Image.open(imname).convert("RGB"))
        #Load in training pictures 

    ims_benign = [read(os.path.join(folder_benign_train, filename)) for filename in os.listdir(folder_benign_train)]
    X_benign = np.array(ims_benign, dtype='uint8')
    ims_malignant = [read(os.path.join(folder_malignant_train, filename)) for filename in os.listdir(folder_malignant_train)]
    X_malignant = np.array(ims_malignant, dtype='uint8')
    ims_basal = [read(os.path.join(folder_basal_train, filename)) for filename in os.listdir(folder_basal_train)]
    X_basal = np.array(ims_basal, dtype='uint8')

    # Load in testing pictures
    ims_benign = [read(os.path.join(folder_benign_test, filename)) for filename in os.listdir(folder_benign_test)]
    X_benign_test = np.array(ims_benign, dtype='uint8')
    ims_malignant = [read(os.path.join(folder_malignant_test, filename)) for filename in os.listdir(folder_malignant_test)]
    X_malignant_test = np.array(ims_malignant, dtype='uint8')
    ims_basal = [read(os.path.join(folder_basal_test, filename)) for filename in os.listdir(folder_basal_test)]
    X_basal_test = np.array(ims_basal, dtype='uint8')


    # Create labels
    y_benign = np.zeros(X_benign.shape[0])
    y_malignant = np.ones(X_malignant.shape[0])
    y_basal = np.ones(X_basal.shape[0])

    y_benign_test = np.zeros(X_benign_test.shape[0])
    y_malignant_test = np.ones(X_malignant_test.shape[0])
    y_basal_test = np.ones(X_basal_test.shape[0])
    
    # Write the Entire Data into a Pickle File
    pickle_out = open("skin-care-detection\X_benign",'wb')
    pickle.dump(X_benign, pickle_out)
    pickle_out.close()
    
    pickle_out = open("skin-care-detection\y_benign",'wb')
    pickle.dump(y_benign, pickle_out)
    pickle_out.close()
    
    pickle_out = open("skin-care-detection\X_benign_test",'wb')
    pickle.dump(X_benign_test, pickle_out)
    pickle_out.close()
    
    pickle_out = open("skin-care-detection\y_benign_test",'wb')
    pickle.dump(y_benign_test, pickle_out)
    pickle_out.close()
    
    pickle_out = open("skin-care-detection\X_malignant",'wb')
    pickle.dump(X_malignant, pickle_out)
    pickle_out.close()
    
    pickle_out = open("skin-care-detection\y_malignant",'wb')
    pickle.dump(y_malignant, pickle_out)
    pickle_out.close()
    
    pickle_out = open("skin-care-detection\X_malignant_test",'wb')
    pickle.dump(X_malignant_test, pickle_out)
    pickle_out.close()
    
    pickle_out = open("skin-care-detection\y_malignant_test",'wb')
    pickle.dump(y_malignant_test, pickle_out)
    pickle_out.close()
    
    pickle_out = open("skin-care-detection\X_basal",'wb')
    pickle.dump(X_basal, pickle_out)
    pickle_out.close()
    
    pickle_out = open("skin-care-detection\y_basal",'wb')
    pickle.dump(y_basal, pickle_out)
    pickle_out.close()
    
    pickle_out = open("skin-care-detection\X_basal_test",'wb')
    pickle.dump(X_basal_test, pickle_out)
    pickle_out.close()
    
    pickle_out = open("skin-care-detection\y_basal_test",'wb')
    pickle.dump(y_basal_test, pickle_out)
    pickle_out.close()
    return X_benign,y_benign,X_benign_test,y_benign_test,X_malignant,y_malignant,X_malignant_test,y_malignant_test,X_basal,y_basal,X_basal_test,y_basal_test

# Merge data

X_train = np.concatenate((X_actinic,X_melanoma,X_basal), axis = 0)
y_train = np.concatenate((y_actinic,y_melanoma,y_basal), axis = 0)

X_test = np.concatenate((X_actinic_test,X_melanoma_test,X_basal_test), axis = 0)
y_test = np.concatenate((y_actinic_test,y_melanoma_test,y_basal_test), axis = 0)


# Shuffle data
s = np.arange(X_train.shape[0])
np.random.shuffle(s)
X_train = X_train[s]
y_train = y_train[s]

s = np.arange(X_test.shape[0])
np.random.shuffle(s)
X_test = X_test[s]
y_test = y_test[s]

    ax = fig.add_subplot(rows, columns, i)
    if y_train[i] == 0:
        ax.title.set_text('Actinic')
    elif y_train[i] == 1:
        ax.title.set_text('Melonoma')
    else :
        ax.title.set_text('Basal')

In [10]:
# See learning curve and validation curve

model = Sequential()
model.add(Conv2D(64, kernel_size= (3,3), activation= 'relu', padding= 'Same', input_shape = np.shape(X_train[0])))
model.add(Conv2D(32, kernel_size= (3,3), activation= 'relu', padding= 'Same'))
model.add(MaxPool2D(pool_size= (2, 2)))
model.add(Dropout(0.25))

model.add(Conv2D(64, kernel_size= (3,3), activation= 'relu', padding= 'Same'))
model.add(Conv2D(64, kernel_size= (3,3), activation= 'relu', padding= 'Same'))
model.add(MaxPool2D(pool_size= (2, 2)))
model.add(Dropout(0.4))

model.add(Flatten())
model.add(Dense(128, activation= 'relu'))
model.add(Dropout(0.5))

model.add(Dense(3, activation= 'softmax'))
model.summary()

kfold = KFold(n_splits=3, shuffle=True, random_state=11)

for train, test in kfold.split(X_train, y_train):
    cvscores = []
    scores = model.evaluate(X_train[test], y_train[test], verbose=0)
    print("%s: %.2f%%" % (model.metrics_names[1], scores[1]*100))
    cvscores.append(scores[1] * 100)

    print("%.2f%% (+/- %.2f%%)" % (np.mean(cvscores), np.std(cvscores)))

input_shape = (224,224,3)
lr = 1e-5
epochs = 50
batch_size = 64

model2 = ResNet50(include_top=True,
                 weights= None,
                 input_tensor=None,
                 input_shape=input_shape,
                 pooling='avg',
                 classes=3)

model2.compile(optimizer = Adam(lr) ,
              loss = "categorical_crossentropy", 
              metrics=["accuracy"])
learning_rate_reduction = ReduceLROnPlateau(monitor='val_acc', 
                                            patience=5, 
                                            verbose=1, 
                                            factor=0.5, 
                                            min_lr=1e-7)

history = model2.fit(x = X_train, y = y_train, batch_size=60,epochs= 30, callbacks= [learning_rate_reduction], validation_split=0.2)
In [ ]:

y_pred = model2.predict(X_test)
print(accuracy_score(np.argmax(y_test, axis=1), np.argmax(y_pred, axis=1)))

    json_file.write(resnet50_json)
